description: Legendary German saxophonist and composer Klaus Doldinger, renowned for his iconic soundtracks for 'Das Boot' and 'The NeverEnding Story', has passed away at 89. His family confirmed his death on October 16. Doldinger's career was marked by his passion for jazz and his desire to create emotionally resonant, independent music.
title: Veteran composer Klaus Doldinger, known for ‘The Never Ending Story’, passes away

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma made their return to the Indian ODI side in Perth, but both experienced disappointing outings. Kohli was dismissed for a duck, caught by Cooper Connolly off Mitchell Starc, while Sharma's 500th international match ended with him scoring just eight runs, caught by Matthew Renshaw off Josh Hazlewood.
title: Virat Kohli steps aside, pushes Shubman Gill and Shreyas Iyer to walk first - watch

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Former Tampa Bay Buccaneers star running back Doug Martin has tragically passed away at 36. The cause of death remains unconfirmed, with his family requesting privacy. Known as "Muscle Hamster," Martin was a two-time Pro Bowler whose explosive NFL career with Tampa Bay and the Raiders left a lasting impact. The NFL community mourns the loss of the respected player.
title: Doug Martin passes away: How did the former NFL Buccaneers RB die at 36

author: etimes.in
description: Diwali, the festival of lights, celebrates Lord Ram's return and the triumph of good over evil. Homes glow with diyas and rangolis, filled with sweets and laughter. Beyond its mythology, Diwali signifies dispelling ignorance with knowledge and hatred with love. It's a time for gratitude, forgiveness, and new beginnings, with families uniting and prayers for prosperity.
title: Diwali 2025: 85+ heartfelt wishes, greetings, messages, and quotes

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India's Women's World Cup hopes hang by a thread after a narrow four-run loss to England. Chasing 289, India fell short despite strong performances from Mandhana and Harmanpreet. Now fourth, India must win their remaining matches against New Zealand and Bangladesh to secure a semifinal spot, with their fate also dependent on other results.
title: How India can still qualify for Women's World Cup semifinals - scenarios explained

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: England secured a thrilling four-run victory over hosts India in Indore to reach the Women's World Cup semi-finals. Heather Knight's century powered England to 288/8, and despite India's strong chase, crucial wickets shifted the momentum, ultimately leading to a heartbreaking defeat for the home side.
title: Tears in dugout: Smriti Mandhana breaks down as India stare at World Cup exit

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravichandran Ashwin humorously exposed an impersonator posing as Adam Zampa on WhatsApp, who sought Indian players' contact details. Ashwin playfully engaged, even asking for MS Dhoni's number. This incident follows a similar encounter where Ashwin was tricked by someone claiming to be Devon Conway.
title: 'Do you have MS Dhoni's?': R Ashwin exposes fake Adam Zampa, reveals chat

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A cargo plane from Dubai skidded off the runway at Hong Kong International Airport early Monday, plunging into the sea. The Emirates SkyCargo flight collided with a ground-service vehicle, tragically killing two workers. The four crew members on board the Boeing 747 freighter were unharmed.
title: Hong Kong plane crash: Cargo jet skids off runway into sea; two dead

title: 'May spirit of positivity prevail': PM Modi extends Diwali greetings

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump reportedly urged Ukrainian President Zelenskyy to accept Putin's terms to end the war, warning of destruction if Ukraine refused. During a contentious meeting, Trump discarded battlefield maps and echoed Russian talking points, ultimately declining to supply long-range missiles.
title: ‘Shouted, cursed,’: Trump urged Zelenskyy to accept Putin’s terms— Inside US meeting with Ukraine

author: KUSHAGRA DIXIT
title: Toxicity! Delhi on a wing and a prayer: Why Diwali firecracker smoke may stay all week?

author: TNN
description: A businessman's son, Jainam Shah, faces charges for assaulting a police officer during a raid on a birthday party where liquor was allegedly served. The incident, captured on video, led to Jainam's booking under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita. His father, Samir Shah, was previously arrested for liquor possession at the same event.
title: Viral video: Surat teen booked for assaulting cop during raid; bizman father held
